document_api_meta.title: Query Target Collaboration Detail
document_api_meta.env_desc: This API is used by Sellers to get target collaboration information.

request_header_param.name: x-tts-access-token
request_header_param.desc: The seller access_token value from [Get Access Token](https://partner.tiktokshop.com/docv2/page/678e3a3292b0f40314a92d75#Get%20Access%20Token%20API), when user_type = 0. Follow this [guide](https://partner.tiktokshop.com/docv2/page/678e3a344ddec3030b238fa0) to get seller access_token.

request_query_param.name: app_key
request_query_param.desc: Every single app will have a unique key. Please use the specific key assigned to your app.

request_query_param.name: sign
request_query_param.desc: Signature generated by gen algorithm. When you send API requests to TTS, you must sign them so that TTS can identify the senders.

request_query_param.name: timestamp
request_query_param.desc: Unix timestamp GMT (UTC+00:00). This timestamp is used across all API requests. Developers can use this convert to local time.

request_query_param.name: shop_cipher
request_query_param.desc:
Use this property to pass shop information in requesting the API. Failure in passing the correct value when requesting the API for cross-border shops will return incorrect response. 
Get by API [Get Authorization Shop](https://partner.tiktokshop.com/docv2/page/6507ead7b99d5302be949ba9?external_id=6507ead7b99d5302be949ba9)

response_param.name: code
response_param.desc: The success or failure status code returned in API response.

response_param.name: message
response_param.desc: The success or failure messages returned in API response. Reasons of failure will be described in the message.

response_param.name: request_id
response_param.desc: Request log

response_param.name: data
response_param.desc: Specific return information

response_param.name: ^target_collaboration
response_param.desc: Target Collaboration detail.

response_param.name: ^^id
response_param.desc: Target collaboration ID.

response_param.name: ^^name
response_param.desc: Target collaboration name.

response_param.name: ^^message
response_param.desc: Message seller has sent to creators about seller's  introduction and why excited to collaborate.

response_param.name: ^^seller_contact_info
response_param.desc: Contact information for the seller in the target collaboration.

response_param.name: ^^^email
response_param.desc: Seller's email contact information.

response_param.name: ^^start_time
response_param.desc: The start time of the target collaboration.

response_param.name: ^^end_time
response_param.desc: The end time of the target collaboration.

response_param.name: ^^update_time
response_param.desc: The update time of the target collaboration.

response_param.name: ^^creator_invited_count
response_param.desc:
The count of creators invited in the target collaboration.
The count will only include the NORMAL state.

response_param.name: ^^showcase_creator_count
response_param.desc:
This field indicates the number of creators who added the product to the showcase from target collaboration.
The count will only include the NORMAL state.

response_param.name: ^^content_creator_count
response_param.desc:
The number of creators who posted content featuring products from target collaboration.
The count will only include the NORMAL state.

response_param.name: ^^product_count
response_param.desc:
The count of products added in the target collaboration.
The count will only include the NORMAL state.

response_param.name: ^^free_sample_rule
response_param.desc: The free sample rules set by the seller in the target collaboration.

response_param.name: ^^^has_free_sample
response_param.desc: If true, free samples are provided to creators invited to the target collaboration group.

response_param.name: ^^^is_sample_approval_exempt
response_param.desc:
If true, creators invited to the target collaboration are exempt from seller review and will automatically be approved for a free sample.
Note that if has_free_sample=false, this field will not take effect.

response_param.name: ^^products
response_param.desc: The information of products in the target collaboration.

response_param.name: ^^^id
response_param.desc: The product identifier.

response_param.name: ^^^main_image_url
response_param.desc: The product image url.

response_param.name: ^^^title
response_param.desc: The product name.

response_param.name: ^^^original_price
response_param.desc: The original price of the product.

response_param.name: ^^^^currency
response_param.desc: The currency code.

response_param.name: ^^^^minimum_amount
response_param.desc: The lowest original price of all SKUs of the product.

response_param.name: ^^^^maximum_amount
response_param.desc: The highest original price of all SKUs of the product.

response_param.name: ^^^commission
response_param.desc: Commission info.

response_param.name: ^^^^rate
response_param.desc: The commission rate in hundredths of a percent. For example, 3587 is a commission rate of 35.87%. This value must a minimum of 1000.  The range of this value is [100, 8000].

response_param.name: ^^^^effective_time
response_param.desc: Commission effective time. It is a timestamp.

response_param.name: ^^^^currency
response_param.desc: The currency code.

response_param.name: ^^^^minimum_amount
response_param.desc: The minimum estimated commission amount for all SKUs of this product.

response_param.name: ^^^^maximum_amount
response_param.desc: The maximum estimated commission amount for all SKUs of this product.

response_param.name: ^^^^shop_ads_commission_rate
response_param.desc:
The commission rate applies only to orders generated from ads. If a creator’s video is used as an ad without this rate being set, the resulting orders will instead earn either:
- The Shop Ads commission you configured in open collaboration, or
- The standard commission defined in this invitation.
The commission rate is specified in increments of 1/10,000.
For example, 1000 stands for 0.1 or 10%.

response_param.name: ^^^status
response_param.desc:
Product's status.
Field values:
- LIVE: When the product is normal for sale, return to the LIVE status
- OUT_OF_STOCK: When the product is out of stock for the consumer, the OUT_OF_STOCK state is returned
- SELLER_DEACTIVATE:  When the product is deactivated by the merchant, the SELLER_DEACTIVATE status is returned
- PLATFORM_DEACTIVATE: When the product is deactivated by the platform or is not available for sale, the PLATFORM_DEACTIVATE status is returned
- GNE_REJECT: When the product is governed or the target collaboration is dismissed, the GNE_REJECT state is returned
- DELETE: When the product is deleted, the DELETE status is returned
- OTHER: When the product is in an unsaleable state, such as draft, frozen, review, etc, the OTHER status is returned

response_param.name: ^^^commission_effective_status
response_param.desc:
The effectiveness of the creators' commissions and products.
Field values:
- EFFECTIVE_ALL: The current product commission is effective for all creators.
- EFFECTIVE_PARTIALLY: The current product commission are effective for some creators.
- EFFECTIVE_NONE: The current product commission is not effective for all creators.
Normally, the commission for a product will be the same for all creators.
If the merchant participates in TOP_CREATOR_PROGRAM, and TOP_CREATOR_PROGRAM includes the current product and some creators, the commission rate will be based on TOP_CREATOR_PROGRAM. The product commission under the current Target Collaboration will be effective for some creators, corresponding to EFFECTIVE_PARTIALLY status.

response_param.name: ^^^collaboration_status
response_param.desc:
The status of the product in the current target cooperation.
Field values:
- NORMAL: The status of the product in the current target collaboration is normal.
- DELETING: The status of the product in the current target collaboration is deleting.Product in the DELETING state will end their delayed effectiveness state and move to the DELETED state at 00:00 the next day.
- DELETED: The status of the product in the current target collaboration is deleted.

response_param.name: ^^creators
response_param.desc: The information of creators in the target collaboration.

response_param.name: ^^^username
response_param.desc: The TikTok user name.

response_param.name: ^^^nickname
response_param.desc: The TikTok nick name.

response_param.name: ^^^avatar
response_param.desc: Data associated with the TikTok creator's profile avatar.

response_param.name: ^^^^url
response_param.desc: The URL for the TikTok creator's avatar image file.

response_param.name: ^^^selection_region
response_param.desc: The regions in which the creator is eligible to promote products in showcases, videos, and live streams.

response_param.name: ^^^showcase_product_count
response_param.desc:
This field indicates the number of products creator has added  to the showcase from target collaboration.
The count includes NORMAL and DELETING states.

response_param.name: ^^^content_product_count
response_param.desc:
This field indicates the number of products creator has posted video or live from target collaboration.
The count includes NORMAL and DELETING states.

response_param.name: ^^^collaboration_status
response_param.desc:
The status of the creator in the current target cooperation.
Field values:
- NORMAL: The status of the creator in the current target collaboration is normal.
- DELETING: The status of the creator in the current target collaboration is deleting.The creator's product promotion relationship in the DELETING status will end the delayed effectiveness status and flow to the DELETED status at 00:00 the next day.
- DELETED: The status of the creator in the current target collaboration is deleted.

response_param.name: ^^^product_effective_status
response_param.desc:
The effectiveness of the creators' commissions and products.
Field values:
- EFFECTIVE_ALL: The current product commission is effective for all creators.
- EFFECTIVE_PARTIALLY: The current product commission are effective for some creators.
- EFFECTIVE_NONE: The current product commission is not effective for all creators.
Normally, the commission rate for all products under Target Collaboration is effective.
If the merchant participates in TOP_CREATOR_PROGRAM, and TOP_CREATOR_PROGRAM includes the current creator and some products, the commission rate will be based on TOP_CREATOR_PROGRAM. The products' commission under the current Target Collaboration will only be partially effective for the creator, corresponding to EFFECTIVE_PARTIALLY status.

response_param.name: ^^^creator_open_id
response_param.desc: Creator Open ID. [More details](https://partner.tiktokshop.com/docv2/page/3obfokj6)

response_param.name: ^^type
response_param.desc:
The type of target collaboration.
Field values:
- STANDARD: The target collaboration is created by sellers manually selecting products and creators.
- TOP_CREATOR_PROGRAM: The target collaboration created by seller joining TikTok Shop Top Creator Program, requiring only product submission.

error_code_list.msg: seller cannot access this target collaboration
Internal error. Please try again. If the issue persists after multiple attempts, please contact platform support.

scope_list.package_description: The application will be able to access a Seller's overall TikTok Shop Affiliate Collaborations, including but not limited to collaboration details (e.g., activity, applications, descriptions, and performance), creator participation/engagement results, affiliate links, affiliate orders, and sample rules.
scope_list.auth_info: The application will be able to access your TikTok Shop Affiliate Collaborations, including but not limited to collaboration activity and performance, creator participation/engagement results, affiliate links, and affiliate orders.
